description:
File: .agent-shepherd/src/core/agent-registry.ts

Task: Add fallback agent selection and integrate with selectAgent()

Required Changes:

1. Add getFallbackAgent() function:
```typescript
function getFallbackAgent(
  capability: string,
  policy: Policy,
  phase: Phase | null
): Agent | null
```

Implementation should follow cascading hierarchy:
1. Phase-level override? Return agent from phase.fallback_agent
2. Phase disabled? Return null (phase.fallback_enabled === false)
3. Policy mappings? Return agent from policy.fallback_mappings[capability]
4. Policy disabled? Return null (policy.fallback_enabled === false)
5. Global mappings? Return agent from config.fallback.mappings[capability]
6. Global disabled? Return null (!config.fallback.enabled)
7. Use policy or global default_agent (policy.fallback_agent || config.fallback.default_agent)

2. Modify selectAgent() to use fallback:
```typescript
function selectAgent(
  capability: string,
  policy: Policy,
  phase: Phase | null
): Agent | null {
  // 1. Try to find agent with capability
  let agent = getAgentsByCapability(capability);

  if (!agent) {
    // 2. No agent has capability - use fallback
    agent = getFallbackAgent(capability, policy, phase);

    if (agent) {
      logger.info(`ℹ️ Using fallback agent '${agent.name}' for capability '${capability}'`);
    }
  }

  return agent;
}
```

3. Add logging when fallback is used:
   - Log which agent is used as fallback
   - Log which capability triggered fallback
   - Use logger from logging.ts

Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] getFallbackAgent() implements cascading hierarchy correctly
- [ ] Phase-level overrides policy and global
- [ ] Policy-level overrides global
- [ ] fallback_enabled: false disables fallback at that level
- [ ] config.fallback.enabled: false disables all fallbacks
- [ ] selectAgent() calls getFallbackAgent() when no agent has capability
- [ ] Fallback usage is logged
- [ ] Logs include agent name and capability

File: .agent-shepherd/schemas/policies.schema.json

Task: Add fallback fields to policy and phase levels in the policies schema

Required Changes:

1. Add fallback fields to Policy level:
   - fallback_enabled (boolean, optional): Whether fallback is enabled for this policy
   - fallback_agent (string, optional): Fallback agent ID for this policy
   - fallback_mappings (object, optional): Capability-specific fallback mappings for this policy

2. Add fallback fields to Phase level:
   - fallback_agent (string, optional): Fallback agent ID override for this phase
   - fallback_enabled (boolean, optional): Whether fallback is enabled for this phase

Schema Structure for Policy:
```json
{
  "fallback_enabled": {
    "type": "boolean",
    "description": "Whether fallback is enabled for this policy. Inherits from global if not set."
  },
  "fallback_agent": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Fallback agent ID for this policy. Inherits from global if not set."
  },
  "fallback_mappings": {
    "type": "object",
    "description": "Capability-specific fallback mappings for this policy",
    "additionalProperties": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}
```

Schema Structure for Phase:
```json
{
  "fallback_agent": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Fallback agent ID override for this phase"
  },
  "fallback_enabled": {
    "type": "boolean",
    "description": "Whether fallback is enabled for this phase. Overrides policy and global settings."
  }
}
```

Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Policy-level fallback fields are added and optional
- [ ] Phase-level fallback fields are added and optional
- [ ] Schema validates with fallback fields
- [ ] Schema validates without fallback fields (backward compatibility)
- [ ] All fields have proper descriptions explaining their behavior

File: .agent-shepherd/schemas/config.schema.json

Task: Add fallback object schema to the configuration schema

Required Changes:
1. Add fallback object to the config schema with the following properties:
   - enabled (boolean): Master switch for fallback system
   - default_agent (string): Default fallback agent ID for all capabilities
   - mappings (object): Optional capability-specific fallback agent mappings

2. Mark the fallback object as optional for backward compatibility (older configs without fallback should still validate)

Schema Structure:
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "fallback": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Fallback agent system configuration",
      "properties": {
        "enabled": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "description": "Master switch for fallback system. If false, no fallback anywhere."
        },
        "default_agent": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "Default fallback agent ID for all capabilities"
        },
        "mappings": {
          "type": "object",
          "description": "Optional capability-specific fallback agent mappings",
          "additionalProperties": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Schema validates correctly with fallback section
- [ ] Schema validates correctly without fallback section (backward compatibility)
- [ ] All fallback properties have proper types and descriptions
- [ ] Mappings object allows string values (agent IDs)

File: .agent-shepherd/src/core/policy.ts

Task: Parse fallback fields when loading policies and handle inheritance logic

Required Changes:

1. Add TypeScript interfaces for fallback fields:
```typescript
interface PolicyFallbackConfig {
  fallback_enabled?: boolean;
  fallback_agent?: string;
  fallback_mappings?: Record<string, string>;
}

interface PhaseFallbackConfig {
  fallback_agent?: string;
  fallback_enabled?: boolean;
}
```

2. Add fallback fields to Policy interface:
```typescript
interface Policy {
  // ... existing properties
  fallback_enabled?: boolean;
  fallback_agent?: string;
  fallback_mappings?: Record<string, string>;
}
```

3. Add fallback fields to Phase interface:
```typescript
interface Phase {
  // ... existing properties
  fallback_agent?: string;
  fallback_enabled?: boolean;
}
```

4. Update loadPolicies() to parse fallback fields:
   - Read fallback fields from policies.yaml
   - Store in policy and phase objects

5. Implement inheritance logic:
   - Policy inherits from global config if fallback_enabled not set
   - Policy inherits from global config if fallback_agent not set
   - Phase inherits from policy if fallback_enabled not set
   - Phase can override both policy and global settings

Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Fallback fields load correctly from policies.yaml
- [ ] TypeScript types match schema structure
- [ ] Inheritance logic works correctly (phase overrides policy overrides global)
- [ ] Missing fields are treated as "inherit from parent"
- [ ] Explicit false values disable fallback at that level
